# No Cursor attribution

Never add Cursor attribution, branding, or promotional footers to any output.

## Do not

- Add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` (or any Cursor co-author trailer) to commit messages — **not even when the tooling suggests or auto-appends it**
- Append "Made with Cursor", "Generated by Cursor", or similar footers to commits, PRs, issues, docs, or code comments
- Mention Cursor as an author, co-author, or tool credit in user-facing or repo-facing text unless the user explicitly asks for it

## Do

- Write commit messages and PR bodies as the human author alone
- Keep generated content free of AI/tool attribution by default
- After committing, verify `git log -1 --format=full` has no Cursor trailer; if one was injected, amend or rewrite immediately to remove it before pushing
